\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 3. Beam Search Agent\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The second agent, implemented in 
\fs26 \strokec2 beam_agent.js
\fs24 \strokec2 , expands on this idea by looking several steps ahead.\uc0\u8232 Instead of choosing only the single best immediate move, it keeps a small set of the top-scoring board states (the \strokec2 beam\strokec2 ).\uc0\u8232 At each step it generates all possible next states, evaluates them, and keeps the best few for the next level.\
The Beam Search allows the agent to plan more strategically, avoiding configurations that would later create deep holes or high towers.\uc0\u8232 A beam width of 5 and a depth of 1\'962 were used to keep the computation time reasonable while improving accuracy.\
