\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 5. Conclusions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The project successfully demonstrates how search-based AI can improve decision making in dynamic environments such as Tetris.\uc0\u8232 While the heuristic agent focuses on immediate board conditions, the Beam Search agent achieves more robust play by exploring multiple possible futures.\
This assignment helped to better understand how evaluation functions and limited-depth search interact in game AI.\uc0\u8232 Future improvements could include increasing the search depth, experimenting with dynamic beam widths, or implementing Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) for comparison.\
